    <!-- About Us Section -->
    <section id="about" class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Story</h2>
        <p>Aro and Everest Entertainments was founded by two driven high school seniors, united by a shared passion for the art of filmmaking. What began as a casual interest has evolved into a deep commitment to mastering the craft, constantly pushing ourselves to learn, experiment, and grow in the ever-evolving world of cinema. While we may be young, we refuse to let our age or limited resources define our potential. Instead, we focus on the boundless opportunities that come with creativity, hard work, and an insatiable curiosity for visual storytelling.

Our specialty lies in the creation of short films, where we explore a wide range of genres and ideas. Each project presents its own set of challenges, and we embrace these challenges as opportunities to innovate. From concept development to post-production, we are hands-on in every aspect of the filmmaking process, striving to make the most of what we have, and constantly finding new ways to achieve high-quality results with minimal equipment and budget.

What drives Aro and Everest Entertainments is not just the desire to produce films, but to craft stories that connect with audiences on a deeper level. We believe in the power of narrative to evoke emotion, provoke thought, and leave a lasting impact. Our goal is to create memorable experiences, using the screen as a canvas to reflect both the extraordinary and the everyday. We approach every film with dedication, attention to detail, and a passion that fuels every frame we capture.

As we continue to grow as filmmakers, we are excited to explore new ideas, collaborate with talented individuals, and push the boundaries of what we can achieve. Our vision is not limited to the present but extends far into the future, where we see Aro and Everest Entertainments evolving into a hub for original and inspiring content, driven by the same passion and determination that started it all.</p>
        <img src="/Users/gavinalsip/Desktop/IMG_8940.jpeg" alt="Our Team" style="width: 500px; height: auto;">
    </section>

